	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=218268><span id= >Phack</span></a><br><span id=notbold>36 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good [4.15]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Tank or not, hitpoints are still the 2nd most important stat for most classes other than tanks, in which it is the most important.<br><br>Ever heard of AE spells?&nbsp;&nbsp;I'm not talking the ones the goblins in HHK have that hit you for 50... I'm talking about ones that hit you for 600hp+.  Some encounters (Grummus, Manatec Behemoth) can be made or broken by how many hp people have.  I'd much rather have over 5000hp with raid buffs than just over 3000.<br><br>How about when a mob enrages and aggro gets messed up and it turns around on the rest of the raid instead of the MT?  That kind of thing does happen for whatever reason... and it helps to be able to take a couple hits before you can turn off auto-attack.<br><br>How about when the MT dies?  What would you rather do?  Run away and get no exp because you have such low hp that you can't even tank a slowed mob for longer than 3 combat rounds and have to run?  Or be able to tank with heals, keep the rest of the group alive, and get exp?<br><br>DEX has diminishing returns as far as how much it helps, just like CHA when buying things.  My Gomdurig procs just as much with 200 DEX as it does with 255 DEX.  I hit just as much as well.  The only thing that affects how much I hit is ATK.  Hence why I said ATK is the most important stat, followed by STR, then HP/STA.  Talk to any rogue over level 55 and if they know what they are doing they will agree.<br><br>I'm not talking about Joe Rogue who is level 25 in HHK.  Before you go spouting off about how I E-Bayed my character, learn something about the high end game, mmkay?</p>&nbsp;<br></td></td></tr>
